turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Hey sweetie.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Hey.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Um.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: How's it- going?  Oh I'm so tired.  Oh, I just woke up. Mmm.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What's going on?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Uh, -Um

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why the sad face?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: they need me out there sooner than I thought

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Where?  Who?  What are you talking about?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They want to deploy me next week.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Next week?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Overseas?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: For--

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: For how long this time?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They said anywhere from two to three years.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What?  What do you mean two to three years?  Don't they know that you have a wife and an expectant child?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I told them that but they--

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Honey--

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: --need me on the specialist honey.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You can't.  We need you.  I need you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I don't want to go but,-

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't care about the money.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: but they said they'd increase my pay by triple-there promotion.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: And you're leaving next week so you won't even be here for Anna's birth?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Do this whole thing by myself?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Honey you're not going to be by yourself--

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: We'll have internet set up, we'll get web cameras and everything.  My whole family's here too.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Carry her for nine months and then yes.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Honey.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's not the same thing.  It's not like having you here.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I can't do this.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can do it.  Alright?  You can, you can be strong, you can be strong for both of us alright?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'm sick of being strong-- --for us.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I don't know what to do.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I don't want to - I don't- I don't want to go.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What am I supposed to do?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You can say no?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You know I can't say no.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You could.  You really could.  You could-- --get into another line of work.  I could start working after Anna's born?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: The last guy who said no was fired.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I put in fifteen years in this job.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I know.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'm so close.  Five more years and I retire-

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: and we'll have that happy life.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Happiness for me is having you here with me

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: and watch our child grow, see her take her first steps, her first words.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Honey after a year I can be back.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You said two years.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They want me there two years but I could probably get

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: maybe get some vacation-- --once it quiets down there.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: A whole year? --We're not talking about like a couple months here.  I mean this is a whole year.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I know.  I know.  But they really need some good guys there.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What could happen in a year?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: And this isn't the first time you know?  I mean you always...sending you off to different places and...

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well that's the kind of work I'm in honey.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't know if that's how I want to live my life.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's just going to be--it's going to go faster than you think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Joe I'm serious I don't want to have to have a little girl to tell...asking every day where's daddy, where's daddy and have to tell her that he's away--

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: far away and he won't be here.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You tell her-- [BREATHING]

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'm done.  I can't honey.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What do you mean?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's over.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Honey I can't do it anymore.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Are you kidding me?  No.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I need you here.  Anna needs you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: So I have--you want me to choose between you guys or my career?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: yeah.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What am I going to do?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Priorities honey, priorities.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I want to--what am I going to do if I leave this job?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're smart.  You could go back to school--

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: finish your Master's that you were started never finished.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Fine.  I'll see if I can talk to them.
